    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n353" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αἰπύς</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εῖα, ύ</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">steep, towering;</span> of mountains,
          towns (here esp. the form <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αἰπεινός</span>),
          streams with steep banks (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αἰπὰ ῥέεθρα, Θ
            369</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 21.9</span></i>, cf. 10), a
          noose ‘hung high,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 11.278</span></i>; met.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πόνος</span>, ‘arduous;’ <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὄλεθρος</span>, ‘utter,’ etc.; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αἰπύ οἱ ἐσσεῖται</span>, he will find it ‘steep,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 13.317</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
